TADS: Therapeutic Advances in Drug Safety is a peer-reviewed medical journal published by SAGE publishers, and can be accessed online without charge. TADS is a member of the Committee on Publication Ethics (COPE). It publishes articles, reviews, and scholarly comment on studies pertaining to the safe use of drugs in patients since October 1, 2010. The journal is aimed at clinicians and researchers in drug safety. The journal's first and current editor-in-chief is Arduino A. Mangoni.
